Extruded Rubber

Extruded Rubber is a versatile material with numerous applications across various fields. It offers exceptional durability, heat resistance, oil and chemical resistance, insulation, and elastity.

Specifications
IngredientsNatural rubber or synthetic rubber
AdditivesGraphite, Sand, Starch, Satalysts, Solorings, Fireproofs
Extrusion temperature150 to 250 degrees Celsius
Pressure5 to 100 bar
Expression speed1 to 10 meters/minute

Processing

  • Safe when using

  • Electrical equipment
